<a id="top"> </a><h1>Tenure-track Position, Ohio State University</h1>
<p>
Assistant or Associate Professor, tenure-track. AOS: Philosophy of 
Science (broadly construed to include formal epistemology and philosophy 
of particular sciences) AOC: Open. Ph.D. required prior to appointment. 
The appointed individual will teach at all levels of the undergraduate 
and graduate curriculum. The current teaching load is four courses per 
year on a quarter system, moving to four courses per year on a semester 
system in 2012. Applications are reviewed as they are received, but to 
ensure full consideration, application materials should be received by 
November 10, 2011. Applicants should submit a letter of application and 
a full dossier including a writing sample to: 
</p>
